member.name: WINHTTP_PROXY_RESULT_ENTRY
member.summary: The WINHTTP_PROXY_RESULT_ENTRY structure contains a result entry from a call to .

member.name: WINHTTP_PROXY_RESULT_ENTRY.fProxy
member.summary: A BOOL that whether a result is from a proxy. It is set to TRUE if the result contains a proxy or FALSE if the result does not contain a proxy.

member.name: WINHTTP_PROXY_RESULT_ENTRY.fBypass
member.summary: A BOOL that indicates if the result is bypassing a proxy (on an intranet). It is set to TRUE if the result is bypassing a proxy or FALSE if all traffic is direct. This parameter applies only if fProxy is FALSE.

member.name: WINHTTP_PROXY_RESULT_ENTRY.ProxyScheme
member.summary: An INTERNET_SCHEME value that specifies the scheme of the proxy.

member.name: WINHTTP_PROXY_RESULT_ENTRY.pwszProxy
member.summary: A string that contains the hostname of the proxy.

member.name: WINHTTP_PROXY_RESULT_ENTRY.ProxyPort
member.summary: An INTERNET_PORT value that specifies the port of the proxy.
